{"questionId":"f196343a-4470-4649-8efb-edf349dd4393_14","correctAnswer":"31","section":"Math","steps":[{"title":"Translate to equations","content":"From $44\\%$ of $h=62\\%$ of $j$, $h=\\tfrac{62}{44}j$. Also $j=\\tfrac{22}{100}k$."},{"title":"Combine the ratios","content":"Substituting gives $$h=\\tfrac{62}{44}\\cdot\\tfrac{22}{100}k=\\tfrac{1364}{4400}k.$$"},{"title":"Convert to a percent","content":"That is $\\tfrac{1364}{44}\\%=31\\%$ of $k$. The answer is <strong>31</strong>."}]}